               <p>197. <persName id="def1-197-18341124" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-197-18341124" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-197-18341124" type="age" value="31"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-197-18341124" type="surname" value="FARNELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-197-18341124" type="given" value="FELIX"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">FELIX FARNELL</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18341124-197-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18341124-197-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18341124-197-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18341124-cd-192" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18341124-197-offence-1 t18341124-cd-192"></join>20th of November</rs>, 2lbs. weight of copper, value 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; and 1/2 lb. weight of brass, value 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; the goods of the <persName id="t18341124-name-1423" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18341124-name-1423" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18341124-197-offence-1 t18341124-name-1423"></join>Phoenix Gas Light and Coke Company</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18341124-name-1424" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18341124-name-1424" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18341124-name-1424" type="surname" value="MCEVOY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18341124-name-1424" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD MCEVOY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the employ of the Phoenix Gas Light and Coke Company. On the 20th of November I was on the premises, and told the prisoner, who was working there, that I was going to Bankside; in<lb></lb>stead of which I stayed and watched the premises—in about ten minutes I saw the prisoner come out—I watched him into a marine-store shop, and</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183411240220"></xptr>
               <p>collared him as he was in the act of taking money for this copper pipe, which was in the scale, but I had before seen it in his hand—we had such copper on our premises—a scuffle ensued—his frock gave way up to the bosom—he slipped it over his head, and ran off.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CHAMBERS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What is the title of the Com<lb></lb>pany? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> The Phoenix Gas Light and Coke Company—the prisoner was a labourer—we had lost copper of this description—I saw this in the pri<lb></lb>soner's hand before he got into the shop—any one might have seen it who was watching him—it was about eleven o'clock in the day—I do not know whether this is called refuse brass and copper—no one had any right to take it away—the men never take any—these are old gas fittings—it ought to remain on the premises—it lays in a heap—it was in a copper kettle, and this was taken from it—I cannot swear I had seen these pieces on the heap—I know the heap was diminished—the prisoner had been about three months there—no one but Mr. Monro had power to give persons leave to take this copper and brass—he is here.</p>
               <p>(Mr. Parnell, a painter and glazier, gave the prisoner a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18341124-197-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18341124-197-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18341124-197-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">GUILTY</hi>. Aged 31.—<hi rend="italic">Recommended to mercy</hi>
                  </rs>.—
<rs id="t18341124-197-punishment-191" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18341124-197-punishment-191" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
